-- Polish Stocks: Budimex, Globe Trade Shares Are Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-01-31T16:59:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/polish-stocks-budimex-globe-trade-shares-are-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  advanced 15.55,
or 0.7 percent, to 2,332.17 in Warsaw, climbing for a fourth day
and closing at the highest level since Nov. 8. The measure has
gained 8.8 percent this month.  The following are among the most active equities on the
Warsaw market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Budimex SA (BDX)   advanced for a third day, increasing
1.8 percent to 85 zloty. Poland’s biggest publicly traded
construction company signed a deal to build an office-housing
complex in Warsaw for 173 million zloty ($54 million), the
company said in a regulatory statement today.  Globe Trade Centre SA (GTC)   jumped 1.8 percent to 10.58
zloty, the highest level since Nov. 8. Poland’s biggest property
developer by market value agreed with its bank creditors to
suspend covenants for 97 million euros ($128 million) of loans,
it said in an e-mailed statement yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
